    "last_activity_date" : 1385211300,
    "last_edit_date" : 1385211300,
    "creation_date" : 1385209902,
    "answer_id" : 20162334,
    "question_id" : 20162145,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p><code>IndexOutOfBoundsException</code> -- if the beginIndex is negative, or endIndex is larger than the length of this String object, or beginIndex is larger than endIndex.</p>\n\n<p>Actually, your right edge of your substring function may be lower than the left one. For example, when <code>i=(size-1)</code> and <code>j=size</code>, you are going to compute <code>substring(size-1, 1)</code>. This is the cause of you error.</p>\n"
  } ],
