  "title" : "String index out of bounds exception java",
  "body" : "<p>I am getting the following error when calling a function from within my class:\n<code>java.lang.StringIndexOutOfBoundsException: String index out of range: -1</code>.\nAlthough I used a system prints to see the inputs I am passing in the <code>substring()</code> function and everything seems to be right. The function <code>isContained()</code> returns a boolean value defining whether the substring passed as a parameter is in a list of words. My code is:</p>\n<pre><code>for(int i=0; i&lt;=size; i++)\n    for(int j=i+1; j&lt;=size; j++)\n        if(isContained(str.substring(i,j-i)))\n            System.out.println(str.substring(i,j-i));\n</code></pre>\n<p>where size is the size of the string (str) I am passing in the function</p>\n"
}